10
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Oh, Darryl, it's brown.

11
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Okay, what is it?

12
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,000
What do you mean? It's brown.

13
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,000
I eat some brown every week.

14
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Hot brown, ice brown, cream of brown, pasta with brown sauce, apple brown, scramble brown, fried brown.

15
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,000
It's brain food.

16
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Poor people are not dumpsters for your garbage, guys.

17
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Well, they should be grateful. This is good food.

18
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:10,000
All right, which is why we are not going home early today and can hang out and have a little Thanksgiving feast of our own.

19
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Yes!

20
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,000
With this canned food.

21
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,000
You son of a bitch!

22
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Don't, Darryl.

23
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Kevin, you're getting it everywhere.

24
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Not even beans.

25
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,000
No.

26
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
I think the point was made and now we're just wasting food.

27
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:34,000
But when Toby gets going, it's just no stopping him.

28
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Happy Thanksgiving. And remember, you did this to yourselves.

29
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
I think everybody learned a valuable lesson.

30
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:48,000
And if I had a Thanksgiving meal with other people for the first time in years, good for me.

31
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,000
You know?

32
